-- Langer Holds 3-Stroke Lead After Senior British Open Third Round
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-07-27T18:17:20Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-07-27/langer-holds-3-stroke-lead-after-senior-british-open-third-round.html
Bernhard Langer shot 4-under par 66
to take a three-stroke lead after the third round of golf’s
Senior British Open.  Langer, 55, is 9 under at Royal Birkdale in Southport,
England, as he seeks to win the senior major for the second
time. The German was tied for the lead after the second round
with American Mark Wiebe, who shot 70 to fall to third place at
5 under.  South African  David Frost  shot 70 to move into second place
at 6 under. Scotland’s Sandy Lyle, Australian  Peter Fowler  and
Gene Sauers of the U.S. are tied for fourth at 3 under. Lyle
finished with 70 today, while Fowler and Sauers both shot 69.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
